  "steps": [
    {
      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Identifying Vanuatu",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "centeredImage",
          "imageUrl": "/images/vanuatu/0_summary_vanuatu.png"
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/vanuatu/vanuatu_locator.png",
              "imageLink": "/images/vanuatu/vanuatu_locator.png",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Vanuatu is an island nation located in the Pacific Ocean, northeast of Brisbane between the Solomon Islands, New Caledonia and Fiji."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/vanuatu/vu_trekker.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/MXbHWAVxi6XCVG6T9",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "All coverage in Vanuatu was taken with a **Generation 3 trekker**."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/vanuatu/vu_soil.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/iF2z775sCKFQC32C7",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The coverage was taken on a volcanic island, and as such you will often see **dark volcanic soil**."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/vanuatu/vu_tropical.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/n1F9nneDAhLeEjvy6",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Vanuatu is a tropical island chain, with a significant part of the coverage being taken in a **dense tropical forest**."
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Regional clues",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/vanuatu/vu_coverage.png",
              "imageLink": "/images/vanuatu/vu_coverage.png",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "Although Vanuatu consists of 13 primary islands, only **Ambrym Island** has coverage. Look for the \u2018Port Vato\u2019 label on the map, north of Port Vila, to find the island."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/vanuatu/Volcano.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/TUdAm2qNf4gVrSXaA",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "This unique **volcano** trekker can be found in the middle of the island."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/vanuatu/Plateau.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/XtQPKEUtEh6N8ZEGA",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "A distinct plateau with **dark brown soil** and **patchy grass** is seen east of the volcano."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/vanuatu/Jungle.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/SwFibjUdmAbs2qoN7",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "Tropical plants and many **ferns** can be seen in this jungle further to the east. A man with a **red cap** is also seen with the trekker."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/vanuatu/Beach.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/V4XG6xGXdyLNzJd99",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "A beach with **black sand** can be seen on the east side of the island."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/vanuatu/Dirt_Road.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/Tv2MdcJnNgLrmzAt6",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "This dirt road with **tire tracks** and slightly purple soil can be seen east of the beach."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/vanuatu/Village.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/TGSzVWFb2dnVy1wn8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "Endu Pahakol, the only village with coverage on Ambrym Island, can be recognized by the small **thatched huts** and dark soil."
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
